documentation.value:
Outputs a message to the web console.

```js
console.log('Hello, world!');
console.log('Value:', myVar);
```

Starts a timer you can use to track how long an operation takes.

```js
console.time('myTimer');
// ...operation...
console.timeEnd('myTimer');
```

Creates a new inline group in the console, indenting subsequent messages.

```js
console.group('Details');
console.log('Name:', name);
console.groupEnd();
```

Transforms a list of key-value pairs into an object.

```js
Object.fromEntries([['a', 1], ['b', 2]]); // { a: 1, b: 2 }
Object.fromEntries(new Map([['a', 1]]));
```

Creates a new Promise object.

```js
const p = new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
  // async operation
  resolve(result);
});
```

Starts the process of fetching a resource from the network, returning a promise.

```js
const response = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data');
const data = await response.json();
```

Sets a timer which executes a function once the timer expires.

```js
setTimeout(() => {
  console.log('Delayed!');
}, 1000);
```

Repeatedly calls a function with a fixed time delay between each call.

```js
const id = setInterval(() => {
  console.log('Tick');
}, 1000);
clearInterval(id);
```

A `WeakMap` is a collection of key/value pairs whose keys must be objects, held weakly (allow garbage collection).

```js
const wm = new WeakMap();
const obj = {};
wm.set(obj, 'metadata');
```

A `WeakSet` is a collection of objects, held weakly.

```js
const ws = new WeakSet();
const obj = {};
ws.add(obj);
ws.has(obj); // true
```

Queues a microtask to be executed before control returns to the event loop.

```js
queueMicrotask(() => {
  console.log('Runs as microtask');
});
```

Creates an anonymous, unique symbol value.

```js
const id = Symbol('id');
const obj = { [id]: 123 };
```

Creates an object that wraps another object and intercepts fundamental operations.

```js
const handler = {
  get(target, prop) {
    return prop in target ? target[prop] : 'default';
  }
};
const proxy = new Proxy({}, handler);
```

Provides methods for interceptable JavaScript operations. Same methods as proxy handler traps.

```js
Reflect.has(obj, 'key');
Reflect.ownKeys(obj);
Reflect.apply(fn, thisArg, args);
```

Declares an asynchronous function that returns a Promise.

```js
async function fetchData(url) {
  const res = await fetch(url);
  return res.json();
}
```

Arrow function expression with concise syntax.

```js
const add = (a, b) => a + b;
const greet = name => `Hello, ${name}`;
```

Wraps code in a try-catch block for error handling.

```js
try {
  riskyOperation();
} catch (error) {
  console.error(error);
}
```

Iterates over iterable objects (Arrays, Strings, Maps, Sets, etc.).

```js
for (const item of [1, 2, 3]) {
  console.log(item);
}
```

Iterates over enumerable string properties of an object.

```js
for (const key in obj) {
  if (obj.hasOwnProperty(key)) {
    console.log(key, obj[key]);
  }
}
```

Declares a class with constructor.

```js
class Animal {
  constructor(name) {
    this.name = name;
  }
  speak() {
    return `${this.name} makes a sound.`;
  }
}
```

Import bindings from a module.

```js
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import defaultExport from 'module';
import * as name from 'module';
```

Export a default value from a module.

```js
export default function myFunc() { }
export default class MyClass { }
```

Export named bindings from a module.

```js
export const myVar = 42;
export function myFunc() { }
export { name1, name2 };
```

Expand an iterable or collect remaining elements.

```js
const merged = [...arr1, ...arr2];
const copy = { ...original, newProp: 'val' };
function fn(...args) { }
```

Access deeply nested properties without checking each level.

```js
const city = user?.address?.city;
const result = obj?.method?.();
```

Allows you to abort one or more Web requests as and when desired.

```js
const controller = new AbortController();
fetch(url, { signal: controller.signal });
controller.abort();
```

Takes a stream of code points as input and emits a stream of UTF-8 bytes.

```js
const encoder = new TextEncoder();
const bytes = encoder.encode('Hello');
```

Represents a decoder for a specific text encoding (defaults to UTF-8).

```js
const decoder = new TextDecoder();
const text = decoder.decode(uint8Array);
```

Generates a random v4 UUID.

```js
const uuid = crypto.randomUUID();
// 'a1b2c3d4-e5f6-4a5b-8c7d-9e0f1a2b3c4d'
```

Declares a block-scoped constant. The value cannot be reassigned.

```js
const PI = 3.14159;
const config = { port: 3000 };
```

Declares a block-scoped local variable, optionally initializing it.

```js
let count = 0;
count++;
```

Write asynchronous code in a synchronous style.

```js
async function main() {
  const data = await fetchData();
  console.log(data);
}
```

Creates a regular expression object for matching text with a pattern.

```js
const re = new RegExp('\\d+', 'g');
const re2 = /\d+/g;
'abc123'.match(re); // ['123']
```

Creates a JavaScript `Date` instance that represents a single moment in time.

```js
const now = new Date();
const specific = new Date('2024-01-15');
now.toISOString(); // '2024-...'
```

Enables language-sensitive date and time formatting.

```js
new Intl.DateTimeFormat('en-US', {
  dateStyle: 'long',
  timeStyle: 'short'
}).format(new Date());
```

Groups elements of an iterable according to a callback function.

```js
Object.groupBy([1,2,3,4,5], n => n % 2 === 0 ? 'even' : 'odd');
// { odd: [1,3,5], even: [2,4] }
```

Declares a resource that is automatically disposed when it goes out of scope.

```js
{
  using handle = getFileHandle();
  // handle[Symbol.dispose]() called automatically
}
```

Create a React function component with JSX.

```jsx
function Button({ label }) {
  return (
    <button className="btn">{label}</button>
  );
}

export default Button;
```
